Raphael Ede, Enugu The Federal Road Safety Corps has confirmed the death of one person in a road crash that occurred on Tuesday in Idodo on the Enugu – Abakaliki Expressway. The state Sector Commander, Mr Ogbonnaya Kalu, blamed the accident on speeding. Ogbonnaya, who didn’t disclosed the particulars of the vehicles that were involved, said three persons were involved in the accident, adding that one died, while two others sustained injuries. He said, “The victims were taken to hospital for treatment while the remains of the deceased have been deposited at the Annunciation Hospital Mortuary, Enugu.” Copyright PUNCH.
